	abstract = {We present an approach to automating software testing using Agentic Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) systems for creating Quality Engineering (QE) artifacts. This approach combines autonomous AI agents with hybrid vector-graph knowledge systems to automate the generation of test plans and test cases. The scope of this paper is limited to the test cases and plan generation. Our approach addresses traditional software test case authoring limitations by leveraging LLMs such as Gemini and Mistral, multi-agent orchestration, and enhanced contextualization. The system achieves remarkable accuracy improvements from 65% to 94.8% while ensuring comprehensive document traceability throughout the quality engineering lifecycle. Experimental validation of enterprise Corporate Systems Engineering and SAP migration projects demonstrates an 85% reduction in testing timeline, an 85% improvement in test suite efficiency, and projected 35% cost savings, resulting in a 6-month acceleration of go-live. © 2025 IEEE.},
