	affiliations = {Universiti Malaya, Faculty of Computer Science and Information Technology, Department of Software Engineering, Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia},
	abstract = {Even while the majority of research uses RAG in modular or microservices designs, many real-world implementations still rely on cloud-hosted, monolithic systems, particularly in the healthcare, education, and corporate sectors. We used PRISMA principles to perform a systematic literature review (SLR) throughout the most popular academic databases Scopus and Web of Science order to look into this understudied field. To address the three study questions - (1) how cloud-based monolithic structures affect RAG integration, (2) which patterns and frameworks are often used, and (3) what advantages, drawbacks, and trade-offs are reported - only 17 peer-reviewed studies satisfied strict inclusion criteria, reflecting the novelty of this research area from 2015 to 2025. Building on these findings, we propose a three-layer reference framework and introduce a prescriptive decision flow that helps practitioners select between cloud-only, hybrid, and on-premises monolithic deployments. This work offers a formal basis for future design, assessment, and deployment of RAG-enabled monolithic chatbots by contributing a uniform reference architecture and taxonomy, in addition to summarizing the research. © 2025 IEEE.},
